  "title": "Bump Konnectivity to v0.0.35 in release-1.25",
  "body": "Bump Konnectivity to v0.0.35 in release-1.25\r\n\r\n#### What type of PR is this?\r\n\r\n/kind feature\r\n\r\n#### What this PR does / why we need it:\r\n\r\nSupports new metrics, logging improvements, and trivial fixes only (no major changes).\r\n\r\n#### Which issue(s) this PR fixes:\r\n\r\n#### Special notes for your reviewer:\r\n\r\n*konnectivity-client (apiserver)*: This bumps Konnectivity to v0.0.35 in release-1.25, but unlike https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/114927 (which merges cleanly), this is a by-hand \"repeat\" of https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/114789 only, in order to resolve conflicts. After this, I would send separate PR to register new metrics. Doing this more conservatively in release-1.25 makes sense (but if reviewers prefer to be in lockstep, I could add commits for the other two PRs here).\r\n\r\n*proxy-server and proxy-agent*:  v0.0.35 consistently with https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/114927. (New metrics, logging improvements, and trivial fixes only (no major changes).\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Does this PR introduce a user-facing change?\r\n\u003c!--\r\nIf no, just write \"NONE\" in the release-note block below.\r\nIf yes, a release note is required:\r\nEnter your extended release note in the block below. If the PR requires additional action from users switching to the new release, include the string \"action required\".\r\n\r\nFor more information on release notes see: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/guide/release-notes.md\r\n--\u003e\r\n```release-note\r\nNONE\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Additional documentation e.g., KEPs (Kubernetes Enhancement Proposals), usage docs, etc.:\r\n```docs\r\n```\r\n",
